    <h4>Description:</h4>
    <p>Baingan Bharta is a flavorful North Indian dish made by roasting eggplants and cooking them with onions, tomatoes, and spices. It’s smoky, spicy, and pairs perfectly with roti or paratha.</p>

    <h4>Prep Time:</h4>
    <p>⏱️ <strong>35 minutes</strong></p>

    <h4>Ingredients:</h4>
    <ul>
        <li>1 large eggplant (baingan)</li>
        <li>1 large onion (chopped)</li>
        <li>2 tomatoes (chopped)</li>
        <li>1 green chili (chopped)</li>
        <li>1 tsp ginger-garlic paste</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp cumin seeds</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp turmeric powder</li>
        <li>1 tsp red chili powder</li>
        <li>1/2 tsp garam masala</li>
        <li>Salt to taste</li>
        <li>2 tbsp oil</li>
        <li>Fresh coriander leaves for garnish</li>
    </ul>

    <h4>Instructions:</h4>
    <ol>
        <li>Roast the eggplant on an open flame until skin is charred and soft. Cool, peel and mash.</li>
        <li>Heat oil in a pan, add cumin seeds and let them splutter.</li>
        <li>Add onions and sauté until golden. Add green chili and ginger-garlic paste, sauté briefly.</li>
        <li>Add tomatoes, turmeric, red chili, and salt. Cook until oil separates.</li>
        <li>Add mashed baingan and mix well. Cook for 5-7 minutes.</li>
        <li>Sprinkle garam masala and mix again.</li>
        <li>Garnish with chopped coriander. Serve hot with roti or paratha.</li>
    </ol>
